{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_31","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `io.netty:netty-codec-xml:4.1.79.Final`. Preserved work is available on `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-4834-fails-native-image-run-io.netty-netty-codec-xml-4.1.79.Final-8f30f1f8`.\n\nThe most likely failing stage was the native-image run in the `metadata-fix` step, not URL population. In `human-intervention-logs/io.netty:netty-codec-xml:4.1.79.Final/metadata-fix/codex.log`, the reproduced failure is `Caused by: java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Can't find '[toLeakAwareBuffer]' in io.netty.buffer.AbstractByteBufAllocator`, followed by `Test for io.netty:netty-codec-xml:4.1.79.Final failed with exit code 1`. The preserved branch adds `metadata/io.netty/netty-codec-xml/4.1.79.Final/reachability-metadata.json` with the two `AbstractByteBufAllocator.toLeakAwareBuffer(...)` overloads, and the same log later shows `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` and `Test for io.netty:netty-codec-xml:4.1.79.Final passed.` `human-intervention-logs/io.netty:netty-codec-xml:4.1.79.Final/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` looks healthy, and `stats/io.netty/netty-codec-xml/4.1.79.Final/stats.json` reports `coveredCalls: 0` and `totalCalls: 0`, so dynamic-access coverage is not useful here.\n\nPlease inspect:\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.netty:netty-codec-xml:4.1.79.Final/metadata-fix/codex.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.netty:netty-codec-xml:4.1.79.Final/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\n- `metadata/io.netty/netty-codec-xml/4.1.79.Final/reachability-metadata.json`\n- `stats/io.netty/netty-codec-xml/4.1.79.Final/stats.json`\n\nNext steps:\n1. Review the preserved branch diff and confirm the added `AbstractByteBufAllocator.toLeakAwareBuffer(...)` reflection entry is acceptable for `netty-codec-xml`.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.netty:netty-codec